==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested around 1439.
* From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abjuracioun|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|abiuratio|abiūrātiō|forswearing, abjuration|lang=la}}, from {{term|ab||from, away from|lang=la}} + {{term|iuro|iūrō|swear or take an oath|lang=la}}, from {{term|ius|iūs|law, right, duty|lang=la}}.
* Compare French [[abjuration#French|abjuration]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌæb.d͡ʒʊˈreɪ.ʃn̩/|/ˌæb.d͡ʒəˈreɪ.ʃn̩/|/ˌæb.d͡ʒʊɹˈɹeɪ.ʃn̩/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/%{b.dZU."reI.S@n/|/%{b.dZ@."reI.S@n/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[abjuring]] or [[forswearing]]; a [[renunciation]] upon oath; as, ''abjuration'' of the [[realm]], a [[sworn]] [[banishment]], an oath taken to leave the country and never to return.
# A solemn [[recantation]] or [[renunciation]]; as, an '''abjuration''' of [[heresy]].

